# Table Indexing & Query Optimization

Indexes must match how `BaseRepository::applyFilters()` queries data.

## Migration — Index Rules

Every table:

```php
$table->id();
$table->foreignId('school_id')->index()->constrained()->cascadeOnDelete();
$table->string('title', 250);
$table->boolean('is_active')->default(true)->index();
$table->timestamps();
$table->softDeletes();
```

| Rule | Example |
|------|---------|
| FK always indexed | `foreignId('school_id')->index()` |
| Filter columns indexed | `status`, `is_active`, `category` |
| Sort columns in composite | `order`, `published_at` |
| Unique lookups | `slug` → `->unique()` |
| Named composite indexes | `news_school_active_order_idx` |

**Composite index column order** = equality filters first, then range/sort:

```php
// WHERE school_id = ? AND is_active = 1 ORDER BY order
$table->index(['school_id', 'is_active', 'order'], 'news_school_active_order_idx');

// WHERE is_active = 1 ORDER BY published_at DESC
$table->index(['is_active', 'published_at'], 'news_active_published_idx');
```

Do NOT over-index: skip indexes on low-cardinality booleans alone unless part of a composite used in queries.

## Repository — Query Rules

Override per repository:

```php
protected function defaultSelect(): array
{
    return ['id', 'title', 'slug', 'thumbnail', 'published_at', 'school_id'];
}

protected function defaultWith(): array
{
    return ['school:id,name,slug']; // always specify FK columns in select
}

protected function searchableColumns(): array
{
    return ['title', 'excerpt'];
}
```

```php
// ❌ BAD — N+1, all columns, no index-friendly WHERE
News::all();
News::with('school')->get();
News::where('title', 'like', "%{$search}%")->get(); // leading wildcard = full scan

// ✅ GOOD — selective, eager-loaded, scoped, paginated
$this->applyFilters($this->newQuery(), $filters)
    ->paginate($perPage)
    ->withQueryString();
```

## Query Checklist

- [ ] `select()` only columns needed by API Resource
- [ ] `with()` every relation accessed in Resource — specify parent FK in child select
- [ ] Use model scopes (`published()`, `active()`, `ordered()`) not raw WHERE in controllers
- [ ] `whereKey($id)` for single-record lookups
- [ ] `LIKE` search only on indexed/full-text columns; prefer `LIKE 'term%'` over `'%term%'`
- [ ] Never `get()` then `slice()` for pagination — use `paginate(15)` max 50
- [ ] Never query inside loops — batch with `whereIn()` or eager load
- [ ] Count queries: use `paginate()` total (one query) not separate `count()` + `get()`

## Index ↔ Query Alignment

Before adding an index, confirm the query exists:

```php
// applyFilters uses: school_id + is_active + ordered scope (order ASC)
// → needs index (school_id, is_active, order)

// applyFilters uses: is_active + published scope (published_at DESC)
// → needs index (is_active, published_at)
```

Run `EXPLAIN` on slow queries in local dev before shipping new endpoints.
